properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 16 at 5:20AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
Strong and gusty southeast winds will develop along Turnagain Arm
and the Anchorage Hillside during the day Monday and peak Monday
night. Gusts as high as 70 mph are likely Monday night. For the
rest of Anchorage and much of the Matanuska Valley, gusty east to
southeast winds of 20 to 35 mph will arrive Monday night. These
winds will cause temperatures across the area to jump above
freezing, possibly reaching the upper 30s to lower 40s. Winds are
expected to then die down during the day Tuesday, with
temperatures cooling back down to freezing or below. As
temperatures cool, the threat for accumulating snow will increase
on Tuesday as well.

There is still some uncertainty with the track and strength of
the storm system causing these winds. Stay tuned to the latest
forecasts by visiting weather.gov/afc.

NWSheadline: Gusty winds and warm temperatures will likely return to Anchorage and the Matanuska Valley late Monday into Tuesday
